race.comment: MOLLY'S MY PAL (6) will find this easier than recent efforts when beaten 3.3L at Ascot last start in a CL3. She is a track and trip winner however and the inside draw can see her close to the speed. Should appreciate the easier company today and can bounce back to winning ways. LEAD BY EXAMPLE (5) disappointed at York last time out when racing over 1920m in this grade, beaten 5 lengths. His recent performances had been better than that, so happy to think that was just a blip on the radar. Can put his best foot forward today. TAK GOES BOOM (8) never really looked likely last start when dropping back to the mile at Ascot following a good run in this grade at York two back. Better placed here and a return to form is on the cards. HIGH PRECISION (3) can sit closer today from a better draw and is not to be discounted. SHE'S RESOLUTE (10) is next best with the visors on first time.
